-- Kasai Kogyo Rises After Nikkei Reports Car-Interior Venture With Chery
-- Kyung Bok Cho
-- 2010-07-09T00:15:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-09/kasai-kogyo-rises-after-nikkei-reports-car-interior-venture-with-chery.html

          
          
             Kasai Kogyo Co. rose the most in five
months in Tokyo trading after Nikkei English News reported the
Japanese company will form a venture in China to produce car-
interior materials.   
 Kasai Kogyo gained 6.2 percent to 308 yen as of 9:13 a.m.
on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, headed for the biggest advance
since Feb. 10. The benchmark Topix index added 0.1 percent.  
          
          


  


        